  "texts": [
    "This definition can be naturally extended to any order n, considering the sequence S n of consecutive overlapping n-tuples present in S 1.",
    "Notice that, if jS 1 j = T, then jS n j = T À n + 1.",
    "We can hence compute the number D n (t) of different tuples among the first t tuples in S n, and extract the nth-order Heaps' exponent β n ∈ [0, 1] from D n ðtÞ $ t β n.",
    "Notice also that the nth-order Heaps' exponent can also be interpreted as the first order Heaps' exponent of a sequence whose events are the overlapping n-tuples of the original sequence.",
    "Finally, it is worth remarking that such an approach is close to the analysis of Zipf's law in linguistic data for ngrams or sentences 61, 62."
  ],
